  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<p><strong>Beginners skiing in Kühtai</strong></p>
<p>Wide, open nursery slopes and easy access in the village means Kühtai is convenient for first time skiers, with plenty of red runs to progress on to.</p>
<p><strong>Intermediate skiing in Kühtai</strong></p>
<p>A selection of wide and open red runs, which are interlinked by a number of lifts, all lead back to the village and your accommodation for an ideal ski in/out experience.</p>
<p><strong>Advanced skiing in Kühtai</strong></p>
<p>Limited but good with three black runs and a lot of off-piste and ski touring available so there is plenty to explore. The forested terrain offers steep but invigorating wooded tracks, ideal for the adventurous skier.</p>
<p><strong>Snowboarding in Kühtai</strong></p>
<p>Boarders will enjoy the k-park with its rails and kickers and the wide, open pistes are great for practising on. During the many periods of fresh snow there is plenty of off-piste to explore.</p>]]></generalInformation>
